org.cloudgraph.hbase.graph

Class LocalEdgeRecognizerWildcardBinaryExpr

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudgraph.query.expr.DefaultExpr
      • org.cloudgraph.query.expr.DefaultBinaryExpr
        • org.cloudgraph.query.expr.DefaultWildcardBinaryExpr
          • org.cloudgraph.hbase.graph.LocalEdgeRecognizerWildcardBinaryExpr
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BinaryExpr, Expr, WildcardBinaryExpr, org.plasma.query.Term

    public class LocalEdgeRecognizerWildcardBinaryExpr
extends DefaultWildcardBinaryExpr
implements WildcardBinaryExpr
    An WildcardBinaryExpr implementation which uses a specific evaluation context to locate or recognize a given sequence based column qualifier within the context of the expression.

    A sequence uniquely identifies an data graph entity within a local data graph and is used to construct qualifier filters to return specific sequence-based column qualifiers and associated column values.

    Since:
    0.5.2
    Author:
    Scott Cinnamond
